# PokePon website deploy workflow

| | Staging (default) | Production (user says “push to production”) |
|---|---|---|
| URL | **https://staging.pokepon.org** | **https://pokepon.org** |
| Branch | `staging` | `main` |
| Command | `bash scripts/deploy-website-staging.sh` | `bash scripts/promote-website-to-production.sh` |

See `docs/WEBSITE_STAGING.md` and `.cursor/rules/staging-before-production.mdc`.

## After website HTML/JS/CSS changes

1. Commit on **`staging`** (or let `deploy-website-staging.sh` commit).
2. **Push to staging website** (always — this is not “production”):
   ```bash
   cd ~/Documents/GitHub/hamiebrooklyn.github.io
   git checkout staging
   bash scripts/deploy-website-staging.sh
   ```
3. Tell the user to verify **https://staging.pokepon.org**.
4. **Do not** push `main` until the user says **push to production**.

## Push to production

Only when the user explicitly asks:

```bash
bash scripts/promote-website-to-production.sh
```

## Bot API

- Website staging push does not deploy the bot.
- After API changes in Poke-Cards: `bash scripts/start-bot-staging.sh` on staging; `deploy-mac.sh` only when the user asks for production.

## Do not

- `git push origin main` for feature work without the user requesting production.
- Stop background bot/tunnel at the start of edits — restart staging bot when ready to test.
